    "The details of corresponding models of X ℓ are given by Eq.",
    "(2.38), Eq.",
    "(2.39) and Appendix C, respectively.Priors on r and A L are imposed as uniform distributions U (-0.2, 0.2) and U (0, 1.2) respectively.The covariance matrix M ℓ used in the likelihood is also derived from the baseline 500 simulations to account for the effects of masking, cosmic variance, noise, and other factors.",
